# File: tests/features/distill-session-skill.feature
#
# Generated from: specs/feature-manual-distill-skill/requirements.md
# Issue: #12

Feature: Manual distill-session skill
  As a Claude Code + Obsidian user mid-session
  I want a manual command that runs the same distillation the SessionEnd hook runs
  So that I can checkpoint a long session without waiting to exit

  Background:
    Given a scratch HOME at "$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/home"
    And a scratch Obsidian vault at "$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/vault"
    And obsidian-memory is installed and setup against "$VAULT"
    And a stub "claude" CLI is on PATH returning a fixed distillation by default

  # --- Happy Path ---

  Scenario: Manual distillation during an active session
    Given a transcript at "$HOME/.claude/projects/my-proj/<sid>.jsonl" of size 5000 bytes
    And the user's current working directory is "/path/to/my-proj"
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:distill-session"
    Then the skill identifies the newest ".jsonl" under "$HOME/.claude/projects/" as "$TRANSCRIPT"
    And the skill pipes a payload with "reason" equal to "manual" into "vault-distill.sh"
    And a new file exists under "$VAULT/claude-memory/sessions/my-proj/" matching "^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}-\\d{6}\\.md$"
    And the note's frontmatter "end_reason" field is "manual"
    And the skill prints the note path

  # --- Error Handling ---

  Scenario: No transcripts exist
    Given "$HOME/.claude/projects/" contains no "*.jsonl" files
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:distill-session"
    Then the skill reports "no Claude Code transcripts found"
    And the skill stops without calling "vault-distill.sh"
    And no new file was created under "$VAULT/claude-memory/sessions/"

  Scenario: Missing jq dependency
    Given "jq" is unavailable on PATH
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:distill-session"
    Then the skill reports the missing "jq" dependency
    And the skill stops without invoking "vault-distill.sh"

  Scenario: Missing claude CLI
    Given "claude" is unavailable on PATH
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:distill-session"
    Then the skill reports the missing "claude" dependency
    And the skill stops without invoking "vault-distill.sh"

  # --- Idempotency ---

  Scenario: Re-running produces a new timestamped note
    Given a previous manual distillation produced "sessions/my-proj/2026-04-19-143022.md"
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:distill-session" again 2 seconds later
    Then a new file "sessions/my-proj/2026-04-19-143024.md" exists
    And the previous file "sessions/my-proj/2026-04-19-143022.md" is unchanged
    And both files are listed under "## Sessions" in "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md"

  # --- Alternative Paths ---

  Scenario: Project slug derived from CWD
    Given the user's current working directory is "/path/to/My Weird & Project"
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:distill-session"
    Then the payload "cwd" field equals "/path/to/My Weird & Project"
    And the hook writes the note under "$VAULT/claude-memory/sessions/my-weird-project/"
    And the skill reports that note's path

  # --- Edge Case ---

  Scenario: Underlying distillation returned empty — fallback stub detected
    Given the stub "claude" CLI is configured to return an empty string
    And a valid 5000-byte transcript
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:distill-session"
    Then the skill reports "fallback stub" for the produced note
    And still prints the note path
    And the skill itself exits successfully
